New Records: The Cavaliers equaled a franchise record set in 1976-77 with their eighth straight win to start the season.
Key Match Events: Darius Garland sank a 3-pointer with 45 seconds left and set up Jarrett Allen for a layup with 12.2 seconds remaining for the clincher.
Garland finished with a game-high 39 points.
Damian Lillard scored 36 points and AJ Green had 21 off the bench for the Bucks.
Green made a 52-footer at the final buzzer, his seventh 3-pointer of the game.
